BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:WifnDuWTjcbyhDsA-CREF
SUMMARY:The Canote Brothers in Concert
DTSTAMP:20260405T040300Z
DTSTART:20260411T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Jere and Greg Canote are identical twins from Seattle\\\, WA wh
	o perform as the Canote Brothers. They are known nationally through their 
	touring and teaching at music camps and festivals across the country. The 
	brothers have played an important role in the old-time music scene on the 
	West Coast through a string band class they have been teaching for several
	 decades\\\, and they are known for their infectious\\\, positive energy\\
	\, and for humorously capitalizing on their relationship as identical twin
	s. \\nThey specialize in old time fiddle tunes\\\, saying “We love the hyp
	notic ‘in the moment’ experience of playing this American Old Time music.”
	 From the synopsis of the recent documentary about them: “Anyone close eno
	ugh to be caught up in this vortex of joy\\\, is likely to end up feeling 
	happier and more optimistic about themselves and the world!” \\nDoors open
	 at 7 pm for the 7:30 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (l
	ower Brick Building). \\nTickets available online or at prior Seattle Folk
	lore Society concerts\\\, or at the door (subject to availability).\n\nhtt
	ps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/the-canote-brothers-in-concert/\n\nFrom P
	hinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/the-canote-brothers-in-concert/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
